From time to time, my acceptance tests will fail because part of the content of fillField gets cut off and the assertion can't match the proper text. I'm not sure why this happens exactly. This doesn't seem to happen when I run the tests with Selenium and an actual Firefox browser, only with phantomjs (in ghostmode) and webdriver.

Here is an example of the test that is run:

```
/**
    * @param AcceptanceTester $I
    * @test
    */
   public function edit_a_valid_personal_interest(\AcceptanceTester $I)
   {
      $I->addPersonalInterest($I);

      // Store the ID
      $interestId = $I->grabAttributeFrom('#personal-interests-list tbody tr:last-child .edit-interest-btn', 'data-id');

      // Edit a personal interest
      $newInterestContent = 'New Personal Interest - edited';
      $I->click('.edit-interest-btn[data-id="' . $interestId . '"]');
      $I->waitForElementVisible('.interest-content');
      $I->fillField('.interest-content', $newInterestContent);
      $I->click('Save Interest');
      $I->wait(1);

      $I->see($newInterestContent, '#personal-interests-list tbody tr:first-child td:first-child');
   }
```

